The paper focuses on interpreting deep visual representations in convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves evaluating the alignment between hidden units and visual semantic concepts, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of interpreted units to provide explicit explanations of CNN predictions, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
